<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-25T14:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-25T14:40:00-05:00" n="798" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00 Revolutions/12: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-25T15:00:00-04:40">February 25, 1930—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:41 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>17. Add to leaders named in my February 24, 4 p.m., Elias Brache,
                            Desiderio Arias and a General Perez, presumably Fermin.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi></signed></closer>
